author: COMSOL
description: This tutorial models how the relative humidity of the inlet gases impacts the performance of a low-temperature polymer electrolyte membrane-electrode assembly. The model includes humidity-dependent ionomer (electrolyte) conductivities, gas-phase mass transport, water ionomer transport and heat transfer. Hydrogen cross-diffusion over the ionomer membrane is also included in the model.
